title: Javascript abstract operations
description: JavaScript's abstract operations are internal algorithms used by the ECMAScript specification to define and describe the behavior of JavaScript features. While not directly accessible to developers, they ensure consistency in language operations. Examples include type coercion, property access, and value comparisons. Understanding these can provide deeper insights into JavaScript's inner workings.

title: Semantic HTML
description: Semantic HTML enhances web content clarity through meaningful tags, aiding both user agents and developers. By using elements like <article>, <nav>, and <aside>, it provides context to browsers and assistive technologies, improving accessibility. Semantic markup ensures web pages are structured logically, benefiting SEO and maintainability.
